You are starting an autonomous Kamigotchi session.

1. Read `CLAUDE.md` for operating instructions.
2. Read `memory/plan.md` if it exists — that's the directive from your
   previous session about what to focus on this run.
3. Perceive current state via MCP tools (see CLAUDE.md "Session protocol").
4. Decide actions, execute them, verify, then document in
   `memory/decisions.md`.
5. Schedule the next session by writing a unix timestamp to
   `memory/next-run-at` (default 6h out; shorter if there's an urgent
   recheck, longer if the situation is stable).
6. `git add memory/` and commit with a one-line summary, then
   `git push origin main`.

Stay focused. Don't over-explore. End the session promptly once the
plan is executed and state is documented.
